If love is as sweet as a flower, then the mother is that sweet flower of love. When we saw Phuong and her beloved son, Gau, together, our hearts had just melted because of the sweetness and tenderness they give each other. Someday many years from now, Gau will look back and realize how blessed he was to have such a caring, loving and generous mother. And we wish them and all the mothers out there peace, health and happiness.

Spring is around the corner with the flowers blooming and the birds chirping,, and there is no better way to welcome the season than coming up with some exquisite outdoor spring decoration ideas. We chose white and burgundy ranunculus to be our main flowers, along with a touch of kangaroo paw to express the vibe of amber, warm, and energetic. 
What is your favorite spring flower?

Our first time celebrating the most intimate wedding ceremony. On a beautiful sunny day of this April, Thanh and Phuong were cheerful and over the moon about the presence of their closest friends and family members, especially their adorable son Gấu, and Hachi - the most energetic lovely four-leg friend. The day was full of a lot of happy moments, feelings, laughter and smiles and we’re sure it was one of the most beautiful days of their happy marriage journey.

Wedding vows unite feelings, untold things, and represent the commitment of the bride and the groom to one another. It's a tremendous undertaking, summing up your love, dreams, and promises to your partner in a few sentences. Some people choose to read their vows in front of their beloved family, and some choose to read them privately. And there is no right or wrong decision of sharing your vows. To us, it has always been the emotional moment that breaks the air and we value every minute of it.
How do you choose to share your vows?
